  <description type="morphology">Plants 30–90 cm. Stems glabrous to sparsely tomentose. Leaves: blades linear to oblong, 10–30 cm, spinose-dentate to shallowly pinnatifid, main spines mostly 5–10 mm, abaxial faces glabrous or nearly so. Heads 1–10. Involucres 3–4 × 3–6 cm, glabrous. Phyllaries: outer and middle bodies densely scabridulous, marginal spinules 0.1–0.5 mm. Corollas purple. 2n = 32, 33, 34, 35.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering winter–summer (Feb–Aug).</description>
  <description type="habitat">Meadows, pastures, old fields, pinelands, usually in damp soil;</description>
  <description type="elevation">0–100 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Ala., Fla., Ga., La., Miss., N.C., S.C.</description>
